ZH: 鼓膜是人耳朵里非常重要的一个部位。
EN: The eardrum is a very important part of the human ear.
ZH: 当你飞机起飞或降落时，鼓膜会受到很大的压力。
EN: The eardrum experiences a lot of pressure when taking off or landing in an airplane.
ZH: 如果你感到耳朵痛或听力减弱，可能是鼓膜受伤了。
EN: If you feel ear pain or have reduced hearing, it may be due to eardrum injury.
ZH: 忍不住揉耳朵可能会导致鼓膜受伤。
EN: Rubbing your ears uncontrollably can lead to eardrum injury.
ZH: 鼓膜会随着声音的振动而产生相应的共振。
EN: The eardrum resonates in response to the vibrations of sound.
ZH: 严重的鼓膜受伤可能需要手术修复。
EN: Severe eardrum injuries may require surgical repair.
ZH: 注意保护好你的耳朵，避免鼓膜受损。
EN: Take care of your ears and avoid damaging the eardrum.
ZH: 鼓膜的主要功能是将声波转化为机械能传入内耳。
EN: The main function of the eardrum is to convert sound waves into mechanical energy to be transmitted to the inner ear.
ZH: 游泳时要小心水进入耳朵，以免伤到鼓膜。
EN: Be careful when swimming to prevent water from entering your ears and potentially harming the eardrum.
ZH: 严重的感冒可能会导致鼓膜破裂。
EN: Severe colds can result in a ruptured eardrum.
ZH: 高音的噪音可以对鼓膜产生不良影响。
EN: High-pitched noises can have adverse effects on the eardrum.
ZH: 鼓膜的损伤可以引起耳鸣或耳鸣加重。
EN: Eardrum damage can cause or worsen tinnitus.
ZH: 鼓膜炎是指鼓膜发生炎症的疾病。
EN: Otitis media refers to the inflammation of the eardrum.
ZH: 使用棉签清洁耳朵时要小心不要触碰到鼓膜。
EN: Be careful not to touch the eardrum when cleaning your ears with a cotton swab.
ZH: 鼓膜有很高的敏感度，可以感受到微弱的声音。
EN: The eardrum is highly sensitive and can detect faint sounds.
ZH: 声音波动的传播过程中，鼓膜起到了重要的作用。
EN: The eardrum plays a crucial role in the propagation of sound waves.
ZH: 切勿用力捏住鼓膜，以免造成损伤。
EN: Do not squeeze the eardrum forcefully to avoid causing damage.
ZH: 注意保持耳朵的干燥，以预防鼓膜感染。
EN: Keep your ears dry to prevent eardrum infections.
ZH: 鼓膜的正常功能对正常的听觉非常重要。
EN: The normal functioning of the eardrum is essential for proper hearing.
ZH: 演奏乐器要注意控制音量，以免伤害鼓膜。
EN: When playing musical instruments, pay attention to controlling the volume to avoid harming the eardrum.
